<div class="inner-subsection">
  <h1>Base Classes</h1>
  <p class="text-lead">Base classes are primarily element and block neutral classes that can apply to anything. They are typically utility classes for commonly used CSS techniques (such as a clear fix).</p>
</div>

<ul class="docs-list">
  
  <li>
    <h2>.clearfix</h2>
    <p>Use this class to clear an element that contains floats. Whether or not this class is output depends on the <code>$class-clearfix</code> and if set to <code>none</code> will not output the class styles.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
    <h3>Example Usage</h3>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;wrapper clearfix&quot;&gt;
  &lt;aside class=&quot;sidebar&quot;&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/aside&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>.remove-clearfix</h2>
    <p>Use this class to remove the styles that would clear an element. Whether or not this class is output depends on the <code>$class-remove-clearfix</code> and if set to <code>none</code> will not output the class styles. This class is typically used when a clearfix is inherited on an element and you'd like it removed.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;remove-clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>.float-left</h2>
    <p>A quick way for floating an element to the left.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;float-left&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>.float-right</h2>
    <p>A quick way for floating an element to the right.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;float-right&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
  </li>
  
</ul>
